The paper focuses on improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for various computer vision tasks such as fine-grained recognition, scene categorization, and visual question-answering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various normalization techniques and their impact on the representation power of CNNs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions visual question-answering, which is a natural language processing task, and thus could also fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses GPU implementation, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
